HEADWORD: Hypocarpium
<hw>Hy`po*car"pi*um</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. <ets>hypocarpium</ets>,
fr. Gr. <grk>"ypo`</grk> beneath + <?/ fruit.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A fleshy enlargement of the receptacle, or for the stem, below the
proper fruit, as in the cashew. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Cashew</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

